<p>Aug. 2. 1917.<br/>Centre for Soldiers Wives &amp; Moth</p>
<p>Dear Mr. Horsfield &ndash;<br/>Can you give Mrs. Bourne (widow) &ndash; some regular assistance as I don't think she is quite up to scale that you assist &ndash; &amp; self &amp; children have been sick. She has a W's account with her &amp; is in need of clothing she tells me.</p>
<p>Yours truly<br/>E. H. Bennie.</p>
